data.enText: to prevent sb from doing what they want to do

data.chText: 她控制这个政党的企图受阻了。
data.enText: She was thwarted in her attempt to take control of the party.

tr: a crosspiece spreading the gunnels of a boat
used as a seat in a rowboat
hinder or prevent (the efforts, plans, or desires) of
example: What ultimately frustrated every challenger was Ruth's amazing September surge

value.def: If you thwart someone or thwart their plans, you prevent them from doing or getting what they want.

example.ex: The accounting firm deliberately destroyed documents to thwart government investigators...
example.tran: 会计事务所故意毁坏文件，阻挠政府调查工作。

example.ex: Her ambition to become an artist was thwarted by failing eyesight.
example.tran: 她想成为艺术家的梦想由于视力衰减而破灭了。
